def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) if isinstance(i, tuple) else i for i in clocs]

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    clevels = [index.get_level_values(i) for i in clocs]
    rlevels = [index.get_level_values(i) for i in rlocs]

    if not rlocs:
        # Adjust handling for single level case
        dummy_index = pd.Index(data.index.levels[clocs[0]])
    else:
        # Properly construct the MultiIndex for the dummy index
        dummy_index = pd.MultiIndex.from_product(rlevels, names=[index.names[i] for i in rlocs])

    if isinstance(data, pd.Series):
        # Handle unstacking for Series
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        # Handle unstacking for DataFrame
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    return unstacked
